          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/15/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>TCM Follow-up</td><td>TCM FOLLOW-UP — 99496 (High complexity)
CC: Post-discharge follow-up, day 7 after hospital discharge
HPI: 42yo female discharged 03/08/2026 from Bon Secours St. Francis for community-acquired pneumonia. Completed 3 days IV ceftriaxone in hospital, transitioned to azithromycin 250mg x 5 days (day 5 today). Reports improved cough, less fatigue. Still some mild dyspnea with exertion. No fever in 4 days.
Hospital Discharge Summary reviewed. Discharge diagnoses: CAP, asthma exacerbation, iron deficiency anemia.
Medication Reconciliation: Verified all discharge meds. Added azithromycin to med list. Confirmed ongoing ferrous sulfate for anemia.
Vitals: T 99.2, BP 118/72, HR 88, RR 20, O2 96% RA (improved from 94% at discharge).
Lungs: Diminished bases bilaterally, scattered rhonchi clearing with cough. No wheezing today.
Assessment:
# CAP (J18.9): Improving on oral antibiotics. Complete course.
# Asthma (J45.40): Stable. Continue maintenance inhaler.
# Iron deficiency anemia (D50.9): Continue iron supplementation. Recheck CBC in 4 weeks. Consider IV iron if Hgb not improving.
# B12 deficiency (E53.8): Start B12 1000mcg PO daily.
Plan: Complete azithromycin. Recheck CXR in 4-6 weeks. CBC in 4 weeks. Follow-up 2 weeks for clinical reassessment. Call if worsening SOB, fever, or hemoptysis.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>01/15/2026</td><td>Patricia Lavinus, NP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Fatigue x 6 weeks, hair loss, dizziness
HPI: 42yo female reports progressive fatigue, hair thinning, lightheadedness when standing. Menstrual cycles regular but heavy (7 days, changing pad every 2 hours).
Labs: Hgb 10.2 (low), Ferritin 8 (very low), MCV 72 (microcytic). B12 180 (borderline low).
Assessment:
# Iron deficiency anemia (D50.9): Likely from menorrhagia.
# B12 deficiency (E53.8): Borderline, supplement.
Plan: Start ferrous sulfate 325mg BID with vitamin C. B12 supplementation. GYN referral for menorrhagia evaluation. Recheck CBC in 8 weeks.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>09/20/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Annual Wellness Visit</td><td>ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT — G0439
42yo female here for AWV.
Preventive Review:
- Cervical cancer: Pap + HPV co-test last 2023. Next due 2028.
- Breast cancer: Mammogram last 2024. Due 2025 — Schedule.
- Colorectal: Not yet due (starts age 45). Due in 3 years.
- Depression: PHQ-9 = 7 (mild). Started escitalopram.
- Anxiety: GAD-7 = 9 (mild-moderate). Counseling referral offered.
Vaccines: Flu given today. All series complete.
Functional: Independent, active.
Advance Directive: Not completed.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
